{"id": 4657, "title": "Ticket #4657: Support EC2 block-device mapping.", "description": "<blockquote>\nSome AWS instance types (those including SSDs, notably) require that the user specify device mappings for them.  Although these mappings are supposedly possible to embed in the AMI, John Hover's VM-creation tools don't support them (and he hasn't managed to get embedded mappings to work yet anyway).\n\n<p>We have support for EBS mapping (which uses a different and incompatible API), so we can look there for a UI.\n\n</p><p>It appears these mappings are specified as additional parameters to RunInstances(), so implementation should be straightforward.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2014-Dec-22 19:03</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/7bfc8ba770e6aad57c050284acee1b36a85590f8\">[42021]</a></span>: minor edit for <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=4657\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('4657'); return false;\" title=\"Support EC2 block-device mapping.\">#4657</a></span>  (By Karen Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2014-Dec-22 18:48</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/de84a4ee7e201e92b5a7d98322945d9d6e37754e\">[42020]</a></span>: Edit existing 8.3.2 version history items for <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=4603\" onclick=